Governor of Delta State, Senator Dr Ifeanyi Arthur Okowa has approved the reconstitution of the Delta State Traditional rulers council with the Orodje of Okpe Kingdom, HRM Felix Mujakperuo, Orhue 1 as Chairman. A statement signed by Secretary to the Delta State Government, Patrick Ukah, disclosed that the new Vice Chairman is the Pere of Akugbene-Mein Kingdom, HRM Pere Stanley Luke, the Kalanama V111 while the Obi of Ubulu-Unor, HRM Agbogidi, Obi Henry A. Kikachukwu, is Vice Chairman. The statement added that the council, which comprises of all gazetted traditional rulers in the state would be inaugurated at a later date.